Brainstorming

1. Deflection of the orbit of an asteroid with laser beam, so that it hit the moon's surface and other missions get the minerals from the moon.
    Problems of this scenario:  If something goes wrong maybe the asteroid hit the earth. The asteroid maybe will burried deep into the moon. 
    
2. Deflection of two asteroid's orbits so that hit each other. And as result we have a new asteroid in orbit around earth.
     Problems of this scenario: Dangerous. Not controlable such a hit.
     
3. Change asteroid orbit for:

    A close flyby that will provide sufficient time for miing

    Entering an earth/moon centered orbit allowing time for total exploitation

