Despinning

    with string attachment

    For a 100 meter diameter asteroid rotating 4 times per day, about 29 tons of fuel would be needed to despin the asteroid.

    with explosion?

    For bigger asteroids, or for a low-budget operation on a small asteroid, it's probably better to let the asteroid keep spinning and just attach the industry to the pole of rotation using a rotary joint.



Tasks
Develop an approach for characterizing the composition of asteroid for mining potential

    Long range spectroscopy and object classification.

    utilizing hyperspectral sensors, the reflected light on each wavelength will be compared against the spectral signature of materials know to be present on asteroids.

    Once materials are identified, an asteroid is classified based on its composition, size, and orbit. This will be used for deciding mining priorities (are we using an automated mining decision system?) 

    When near an asteroid, same type of sensors and additional LiDAR can be used to further analyze the asteroid creating a resource map that will be used to guide the mining process.

    Perform a soundradar scan using attached survey bots creating a 3D reprsenation of the asteroid's inner structure (detecting cavities, possible gas pockets etc)


Explore a possible division of labor involving different types of vehicles

    Water extraction miner robot

    Metal extraction robot

    Material separation robot

    Orbit modification and Asteroid stabilization robot

    Asteroid processing plant (hosts robots and does material processing)

    Cargo transport vessel

